# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PUBLIC SHOWCASE REPO — whitelist model.
#
# This repo is published as a portfolio piece. The implementation source
# (index.html, demo.html, server.js, build-demo.js, demo-src/, versions/,
# demo-deploy/, .env, etc.) must NEVER be committed.
#
# Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING at the root, then explicitly allow only the
# showcase docs and assets below. This holds even against `git add -A`.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1) Ignore everything.
/*

# 2) Allow only the showcase surface back in.
!.gitignore
!README.md
!assets/
